Here's how to implement all three:

### 1. Custom "Cancel" Back Button (in `EditProductPage.xaml`)

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- your form here -->
</ContentPage>
```

### 2. ViewModel back command with confirmation

```csharp
public partial class EditProductViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty] bool hasUnsavedChanges;

    [RelayCommand]
    async Task Back()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "Discard your changes?",
                "Discard", "Stay");
            if (!discard) return;
        }
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

### 3. Guard the hardware/gesture back too (in `AppShell.xaml.cs`)

The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` handles the **Shell back button**, but the Android hardware back or swipe-back gesture fires through `OnNavigating`. Guard both:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard your changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `GetDeferral()` is required because the confirmation is async — without it the navigation completes before the dialog returns.
- Check `args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop` so the guard only fires on back navigation, not forward pushes.
- `BackButtonBehavior.TextOverride` replaces the back arrow with "Cancel" text. You can also set `IconOverride` if you want a custom icon instead.
